SUMMARY:Deadline: Technology Fellow: Digital Safety and Security
DESCRIPTION:The Ford Foundation seeks a two-year Technology Fellow for Digi
 tal Safety and Security to expand the foundation's ability to support gran
 tee digital safety and security. Civil society organizations face targeted
  information security threats yet many lack the resources and training to 
 maintain robust digital security. Reporting to the Director\, Office of th
 e Vice President for U.S. Programs\, the Fellow will identify field-buildi
 ng opportunities in the public-interest digital safety and security field\
 , work directly with program officers across US and global teams to integr
 ate digital security capacity into Ford's technical assistance programs\, 
 provide strategic support to high-risk grantees\, and assess strategic gap
 s in the ecosystem for safety and security providers. The Technology Fello
 ws Program is administered by Ford's Technology and Society Program and is
  designed to increase sociotechnical capacity within the Foundation. Requi
 rements include a minimum of 7 years' professional experience with media\,
  technology\, advocacy or policy organizations\; a baccalaureate degree or
  equivalent experience\; sophisticated knowledge of existing and emerging 
 technologies with a focus on surveillance technologies and organizational 
 digital safety and security\; and experience designing\, implementing or s
 upporting digital safety and security solutions in a complex global settin
 g. Hybrid role based in New York (three days per week in office) with appr
 oximately 10 to 20 percent domestic and international travel. Not eligible
  for visa sponsorship\; candidates must be authorized to work in the Unite
 d States. Submit both a resume and a cover letter to be considered.\n\nOrg
 anisation: Ford Foundation\nLocation: New York\, New York\, USA\nAward: US
 D 166\,000 to 170\,000 annual salary\, plus comprehensive benefits and ret
 irement contributions of up to 13%\nDuration: Two-year term-limited contra
 ct\n\nMore: https://fordfoundation.wd1.myworkdayjobs.com/en-US/FordFoundat
 ionCareerPage/details/Technology-Fellow--Digital-Safety-and-Security_R1295
 ?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://fordfoundation.wd1.myworkdayjobs.com/en-US/FordFoundationCareer
 Page/details/Technology-Fellow--Digital-Safety-and-Security_R1295?utm_sour
 ce=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:New York\, New York\, USA
END:VEVENT
